name: PrescribableBrandAndGenericNonInsulinDrugsForHyperglycemiaInType2Diabetes
title: Prescribable brand and generic non insulin drugs for hyperglycemia in Type 2 Diabetes
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for both brand and generic prescribable non-insulin medications used to treat hyperglycemia in Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus),(Data Element Scope: Any medication data element which references prescribable, non-insulin medications used to treat hyperglycemia in Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus using SBD and SCD RxNorm TTYs),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that describe a generic or branded prescribable medication containing ingredients in the following classes: Sulfonylureas, GLP-1 receptor agonists, SGLT2 inhibitors, DPP-4 inhibitors, Alpha-glucosidase inhibitor. Also includes drugs containing the following ingredients: thiazolidinedione , glinide, pramlintide, metformin.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that describe a non-prescribable medication.)
